Mentilo Terms & Conditions
Effective: July 2025

1. Scope
These Terms & Conditions ("Terms") govern the use of the Mentilo mobile application and any related services operated by Niclas Braun ("we" or "us"). By installing or using Mentilo you agree to be bound by these Terms as well as our Privacy Policy.

2. Eligibility & Accounts
Mentilo is intended for users aged 13 and above. When starting the app, an anonymous user profile is generated and you may optionally choose a username. You are responsible for keeping your device secure and for any actions taken through your profile.

3. Permitted Use
You agree to use Mentilo only for lawful purposes and in accordance with game rules. Automated interactions, exploits, or manipulation of leaderboards and matchmaking are prohibited. We reserve the right to remove suspicious scores, anonymize or block offensive usernames, and suspend access in case of misuse.

4. Virtual Goods & Advertising
Mentilo may offer in-app purchases or rewarded advertising. Purchases are handled through the respective app store and subject to its terms. Advertisements may be personalized based on your consent. Rewards granted through ads or purchases are non-transferable and have no cash value.

5. Intellectual Property
All content, code, graphics, and trademarks within Mentilo are owned or licensed by us. You receive a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the app for personal, non-commercial entertainment purposes. Reverse engineering, redistribution, or commercial exploitation is prohibited unless permitted by law.

6. Third-Party Services
Mentilo integrates services such as Firebase (authentication, analytics, crash reporting, remote config), Google AdMob, Unity Ads, and Meta Audience Network. These providers may process data as described in our Privacy Policy. Service availability may change at any time.

7. Warranties & Liability
Mentilo is provided "as is" without warranties of uninterrupted availability or error-free operation. To the maximum extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use of the app. Mandatory statutory rights remain unaffected.

8. Termination
You may stop using Mentilo at any time by uninstalling the app. We may suspend or terminate access if you breach these Terms or if continued operation becomes impractical due to legal or technical reasons.

9. Changes to the Terms
We may update these Terms to reflect changes in features, legal requirements, or business practices. Significant updates will be communicated in-app or via the app store listing. Continued use after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.

10. Governing Law & Dispute Resolution
These Terms are governed by the laws of Germany. Mandatory consumer protection rules of your country of residence remain unaffected. Disputes will be resolved amicably whenever possible; otherwise, statutory jurisdiction rules apply.

Privacy Overview
For transparency, the following summarizes key points of our Privacy Policy:
- Anonymous user IDs and optional usernames are stored for leaderboards and matchmaking.
- Game statistics are saved locally and partially synchronized with Firestore.
- Crashlytics and Analytics help improve stability.
- Ads are served via Google AdMob and mediation partners. Personalized ads require your consent.
- Remote configuration adjusts gameplay parameters dynamically.
- Ghost Player replays use anonymized performance data only.

You may revoke consent for advertising or request data access, correction, or deletion via bingoscann@gmail.com.

